			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	 I agree. The blockade option should be availabre only in war or in alliance. I'll try to explain what I mean by this. Let's say we have 3 councils A, B, and C to make it very simplistic.<br />
A is at war with B, and they have similar power. C is higher power and has an alliance with B (and can't declare war at A). In this case C should be allowed to send a maximum of 2 fleets to assist the ally, in this case by blockading A. But only if C had alliance with B. This would make the game easyier for new people and would make the game more diplomatic without taking out the war scenario.			   <P align=right></P>
