			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	I could refer us to the other game that Mari came up with, Archmage.  In that game, you could only attack someon no less than 80% of you power, and up to 150% or 200% above you, I forget which.  The point is, 20% power difference gives you somewhat of an edge, but not this overpowering edge we presently have.  <br />
<br />
If on the other hand the honor system actually meant something.... Well, why doesn't it?  If it is a matter of coding, it seems logical that changing the ratios would be easier than implementing new things.  But I don't know, I don't code.  I just do know that the way things stand really suck and are driving off new players who never really get a chance.  <br />
<br />
I think this single issue more than anything totally detracts from what is otherwise a damm fine game.  I would be cool if blockades were completly taken out of the picture.  They don't even make sense.  In real warfare a blockade is a blockage, it hurts your trade, bottles up your ports, there are no attacks or battles unless the guy being blockaded tries to break the blockade or slip ships by it.  This abortion is just a cheap way for people to attack anyone they want.  <br />
<br />
Now the main reason I wrote this was not because I thought the devs would jump right in and change it all just because I don't like it.  But if the rest of you that I hear complaining about blockades would write something here, well, if enough do then the devs would probably make some changes.  They want a game that everyone likes too.  So come on, make a difference, help change things for the better, write your support here.			   <P align=right></P>
